CHAPTER XL.

M. Manlius, the Praetor, lands at Carales. Sets out and encamps near the Camp of Hamspicora. Hamspicora absent, raising new Forces. His Son Hostis, who is left in Command‚ routed and put to Flight. War in Sardinia had been ended but for the Arrival of Has- drubal with the Macedonian Fleet from the Baleares (Ch. XXXIV). Manlius returns to Carales. Hamspicora joins Hasdrubal.
